  "texts": [
    "In order to store Y in some block of the residual stream, the jth row of Y cannot be output into any row of the residual stream more than d -j rows from the bottom.",
    "Intuitively, if Y is to \"fit\" into the residual stream, row j cannot be output at too low of a row in the residual stream: there must be space for at least d -j more rows.",
    "Formally, the jth row of Y must be output somewhere in the ℓ-th row of the residual stream for ℓ ≤ d + j + 1.",
    "However, since Y P = P Y and j < i, Y j is located in the ith row of Y P, which is in row d + i + 1 of the input.",
    "Since d + i + 1 > d + j + 1 ≥ ℓ, by Lemma 1, row ℓ of the residual stream must be invariant to row d + i + 1."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}